# Workspace Health LLM Guide

Use this command to verify that the current workspace contract is readable and internally healthy.

## When To Run

- Before implementing a task in a repository with `.enclosure/`.
- After changing `.enclosure/enclosure.yaml`, `.enclosure/rules/`, or `.enclosure/recipes/`.
- When root `enclosure health` points at workspace findings.

## How To Interpret

- Error findings are blocking; report them and use the focused command named by the category.
- Rule findings usually need `enclosure workspace rules`.
- Recipe findings usually need `enclosure workspace recipe --check`.
- Architecture findings are outside this command; use `enclosure architecture health`.
